title: Osculating circle
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

If
$$\gamma\colon I\to\R^2$$
is a [[regular curve|Regular curve]] parametrized by arclength, i.e.
$$\|\gamma'\|=1,$$
then
$$\gamma''=\kappa N,$$
where
$$\kappa$$
is the curvature. The osculating circle is the circle with center $$\gamma+\frac 1 \kappa N$$
and radius
$$\frac 1 \kappa.$$